{
  "texts": [
    "Given the complex interaction between different building systems and subsystems, design optimization during early design typically requires exploring high-dimensional design space.",
    "Consequently, ML has been used to create metamodels that can be used for optimization and uncertainty analysis (Eisenhower et al., 2012; Bre et al., 2020).",
    "Although most studies predict energy consumption and thermal comfort, metamodels have also been proposed for the emulation outputs such as natural ventilation and daylighting to support the modeling of passive design strategies (Chen et al., 2017).",
    "A comparison of different metamodeling techniques can be found in Østergård et al. (2018).",
    "Moving from design to postoccupancy, model calibration is often undertaken to improve the model's credibility by reducing the discrepancies between simulation predictions and actual observations."
  ]
}